SIMPLE: multiplier
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Multiplier
<hw>Mul"ti*pli`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>multiplier</ets>. Cf. <er>Multiplicator</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, multiplies or increases number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>The number by which another
number (the <corr>multiplicand</corr>) is multiplied. See the Note under
<er>Multiplication</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for multiplying
or increasing by repetition or accumulation the intensity of a force or
action, as heat or electricity. It is particularly used to render such a
force or action appreciable or measurable when feeble. See
<er>Thermomultiplier</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Multiply</ent>⟦br⟧
